						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is too fragmentary.</p>						

						<p>It appears to record a gift of land to provide for burning a lamp, for feeding in the <hi rend="italic">tiruchchuṟṟu-māḷigai</hi> during the midday worship, and other services (details lost) probably in the temple of the god at Tirunallam. The land was made tax-free by the <hi rend="italic">sabhai</hi> of the place and the signatory by order of the <hi rend="italic">sabhai</hi> was Śiri-Āritan.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
